INSERT INTO `main_comment` VALUES (2,1,'Tom Bosschaert','www.except.nl','Polydome reached the semi-finals of the Buckminster Fuller Challenge! Read more at http://challenge.bfi.org/.','2012-05-25 08:43:33'),(4,95,'Tijn','','Nice book! Very cool.','2012-04-13 16:31:54'),(6,66,'Tijn','','Wow, look at your articles! Love the lightwave guide... thanks. ^_^','2012-04-14 09:21:45'),(100,1,'Tom Bosschaert','www.except.nl','We just added the polydome book for download. Enjoy!','2012-07-13 19:23:16'),(103,204,'Roger Brewster, BSc, MTP','roger.brewster@gmail.com','firstly as an environmental planner, I think your definition warrants serious consideration and therefore promotion and discussion. On a point of detail the Object Indicators could include the built environment as a separate object, or related to and a combination of energy, materials and economy.  ','2012-08-06 05:31:05'),(104,204,'Tom Bosschaert','tom@except.nl','Thanks, Roger, for your insightful comment. The built environment certainly warrants specific considderation. In the Object set, which in the diagram above uses the ELSIA categorisation, the built environment is part of the \'culture\' subsection, as much as for instance \'transport\' is part of the \'economy\' section. These are subsets of the categorisation which we include in more fine grained categorisation listsings which we generate using ELSIA.  There\'s more info in the article concerning ELSIA elsewhere on the site, but it might be useful for us to show an expanded set of categorisation from ELSIA8. I\'ll look into that.','2012-08-07 00:11:02'),(105,204,'Gary Wain','gary@moulding-solutions.co.uk','This is an excellent article.  However where does cost come into the equation?  If you cannot make something sustainable due to the high cost, then do you make it at all?\n','2012-08-09 14:01:54'),(106,149,'Jeroen Graave','jeroen.graave@aardevast.nl','ELSIA is een interessante indeling; ik ben voor mijn kersverse organisatie adviesbureau nog zoekende naar een samenhangende methode voor duurzaamheid en vind op de site van Except veel inspiratie. Ik heb moeite met de \" individual\" laag; hij verwijst teveel naar het huidige, westerse denken. Wat als je die weglaat en de overige drie lagen beschouwd als  micro (individual) en macro (netwerk)  \"parts\"?','2012-08-13 12:15:31'),(107,204,'Ken Melamed','ken@kenmelamed.com','I especially appreciated the comments on the Bruntland \"definition. Well done. The SiD approach is similar to the Natural Step Framework, particularly the strategic step by step approach. \nthank you','2012-08-15 17:55:44'),(110,201,'Tom Bosschaert','tom@except.nl','I love this game! the drawings are great, and it really teaches you about waste water innovations.','2012-08-28 18:26:28'),(109,14,'Mark Seftel','mseftel@gmail.com','Can this be done here: http://www.mabonengprecinct.com/\n\nor here:\n\nhttp://goo.gl/maps/uo3So','2012-08-19 10:25:23'),(111,91,'Jon Wiggins','jnwiggins0202@gmail.com','I am a Masters student in Architecture at Ball State University and am looking into the research that has been done to support this concept. I am specifically interested in the data that supports the claim that the farms can be built to use little or no energy from external sources. The ref link directs me to a site that also does not have the hard data posted. Is this or can this data be made available to me?\n\nMany Thanks,\n\nJon Wiggins','2012-09-06 17:42:07'),(112,91,'Tom Bosschaert','','Thanks Jon, for your question.\nThat data came from various research documents from the university of Columbia. Since them, we\'ve calculated various urban farm strategies in terms of energy and material use. In many cases they can be made energy neutral, but if the growing system relies on artificial light as a major photon resource for growth, this becomes difficult. \nMost energy can be collected by gassifying the biomass waste from the harvest and afterwards. This gas is then used to drive cogen plants to deliver heat and electricity.','2012-09-10 20:19:32'),(113,1,'Paul Pawlowski','prvp7787@gmail.com','Please add me to your mailing list','2012-09-20 06:18:24'),(119,154,'Rien','','Goed hulp boek','2013-01-01 19:17:49'),(120,148,'Mike Thompson','mike.thompson761@gmail.com','I am very impressed by this holistic approach. I am part of an MSc development team who are working on the sustainability process and I am  keen to pursue this methodology.  ','2013-01-12 11:25:30'),(121,148,'Mike Thompson','mike.thompson761@gmail.com','I am very impressed by this holistic approach. I am part of an MSc development team who are working on the sustainability process and I am  keen to pursue this methodology.  ','2013-01-12 11:25:53'),(122,148,'InÃªs Costa','http://pt.linkedin.com/in/inescosta/','Congrats on the website and on your approach. I can find parallels with two approaches: one is the middle-out model that I have described for developing Industrial Symbiosis (I have a paper about it published with the JCP) and also the concept of Living Labs - http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Living_lab . ','2013-01-18 11:51:22'),(123,149,'Tom Bosschaert','','Thanks for your comment, Jeroen.\nWe\'ve had conversations about this before. This focused on whether or not ELSIA was antropocentric or not.  When conceving of it, we made sure not to define who or what this \'individual\' is. It may very well be an animal.\n\nAs such, the \'individual\' element represents each and every individual entity in our world, and as such is neither anthropocentric nor focusing on a particular single individual.\n\nThis does requires those that use and work with ELSIA to have this state of mind. As with everything, SiD and ELSIA can be used in correct and incorrect ways.','2013-02-02 04:33:48'),(124,92,'paul spiers','spiers_paul@hotmail.com','i was looking for an LED that had a wide spectrum of light, as close to natural sunlight as possible, to grow plants in aquariums. excellent article by the way.\nyou might add a piece to this document that could recommend different lights for different applications, sources, etc','2013-02-14 23:47:47'),(125,92,'paul spiers','spiers_paul@hotmail.com','addendum: i have found that breeding tropical fish is more successful under lights that have spectrums of light closer to natural light. i combine this with dark sided tanks (or wooden) to limit there fear of detection (by predators).\nmay i submit it for print in \"Aqua Antics\". an aquqrium society in Sarnia, Ontario, Canada. if not perhaps, i could just print the link and let them find it themslves.  thank you, cheers','2013-02-14 23:56:42'),(126,229,'Tim Horsten','tim@except.nl','Als mede organisator van deze avond vond ik het heel spijtig op tijd weg te moeten. Ik had het nog prima naar mijn zin !','2013-02-19 12:40:55'),(127,215,'Tim Horsten','tim@except.nl','Een certificaat zie ik als een mooie houvast \'in den beginne\'. Zolang het daarna maar niet beperkend wordt, waar het gaat om innovatie en creativiteit. Verduurzaming kan namelijk heel mooie dingen opleveren, zolang het maar in de volle breedte beschouwd wordt.','2013-02-19 12:45:16'),(128,204,'Tim Horsten','tim@except.nl','Het is verschrikkelijk moeilijk heb ik gemerkt om kort en bondig te omschrijven waar duurzaamheid over gaat. The SiD Definition is de meest complete die ik tot nu toe heb gezien. Een andere, nog kortere omschrijving die naar mijn smaak de lading nog steeds dekt is jezelf continu de vraag stellen; \"Is het bestemd om te duren ?\"','2013-02-19 12:53:44'),(129,236,'Erik','erik@except.nl','Ha! What a great weekend!','2013-02-20 17:01:46'),(130,201,'Yasmin','ykhan@embarqmexico.org','Do you have it in other languages?\n','2013-04-05 22:49:05'),(131,241,'C.H.Lee','incabliss@hotmail.com','Wonder concept6 for now and the future.\nPlease carry on.Thanking you Kind regards\nC.H.Lee','2013-04-27 21:25:09'),(132,241,'C.H.Lee','incabliss@hotmail.com','Wonder concept for now and the future.\nPlease carry on.Thanking you Kind regards\nC.H.Lee','2013-04-27 21:26:30'),(133,262,'Adrie Otte','adrie@bioniers.nl','Great article. Of course ecologists already know this and use systems thinking all the time to restore ecosystems or create useful ecosystems that can do useful things for us (ecological engineering).','2013-06-03 11:39:24'),(134,262,'Erik','erik@except.nl','Thanks Adrie! True, and there\'s a lot to learn from ecology. Are you experienced in applying a systems approach for societal problems or organizational strategy?','2013-06-03 17:19:14'),(135,253,'Sambhav Kothari','vxlnigeria@gmail.com','Fantastic! Would have interests in Africa? Nigeria to be precise. How much would a 11,700 sq. ft area cost (rough estimate)? Plenty of empty abandoned warehouses scattered all over the country. Plenty potential. \nPlease confirm. Regards.','2013-06-04 23:38:11'),(136,149,'Brent Auvermann','b-auvermann@tamu.edu','I love this typology.  But I don\'t think it\'s necessary to apologize for, or to disavow, any implied anthropocentrism (cf. Jeroen\'s comment).  The jaguars and fungi are going to have a hard time thinking through - together! - what sorts of arrangements will be required to ensure that their _homo_sapiens_ friends are not rendered extinct.  That\'s OUR job, among other things.','2013-06-10 22:50:37'),(137,264,'Marijke van Loon','vanloonkleuradvies@gmail.com','Geachte heer/mevrouw,\n\nKomt visuele duurzaamheid ook aan de orde? Persoonlijk ken ik in Nederland maar een plaats (Delft) en een woningcorporatie (Oldenzaal) die bewust bezig zijn met een beeldkwaliteitsplan voor hun omgeving. \nMet een vriendelijke groet,\n\nMarijke van Loon','2013-06-17 16:13:00'),(138,269,'Sandra Hoomans','sanhoom@gmail.com','Dit past precies bij mijn PhD onderzoek naar besluitvorming en implementatie van besluiten mbt gebiedsontwikkeling (op basis van de drie dimensies van duurzaamheid)....heel interessant. Ik ga kijken of ik mee kan!','2013-07-09 15:37:56'),(139,278,'Kwazai','kwazai99@gmail.com','Some real dependence on technology appearing. What\'s wrong with solar/wind to pump water up to the top of an elevator like atrium greenhouse on a skyscraper? Actually makes more sense as a glass urban warehouse with gravity water flow to lighten the work load.\n','2013-07-24 04:41:47'),(140,278,'Kwazai','kwazai99@gmail.com','The green vegetation vs. brownout areas is due mostly to water. ie- Turkey controlling the euphrates, israel and syria over the  jordan basin under the dead sea, the kashmir dam, etc.\nReal impacts only gonna be made by \'watering the desert\'.','2013-07-24 04:43:42'),(141,90,'Hassan Salih','hasdzyn@gmail.com','Very interesting article. Could not see the figures talked about however and the links are not live links.','2013-08-12 23:15:25'),(142,91,'Jenna','jenna.m.smith@gmail.com','As a Masters student in Agroecology, I\'m very interested in these ideas, and I fully support  exploration of urban-based solutions for our food needs. I\'m wondering about the dilemma in energy cycling vs. nutrient cycling that rises from the methods you discuss in large-scale implementation.  If you are gassifying biomass waste to convert carbon into heat and electricity, aren\'t you also disrupting nitrogen, phosphorus and other nutrient cycling?  This can\'t be a truly closed system if you are not only exporting agricultural products, but also using compost waste in a process that is ~80% energy efficient...and you\'re losing valuable nitrogen & phosphorus resources in the process...\n\nIs it possible to design such an urban farm so that it doesn\'t rely on energy OR nutrient inputs?  You mention treating waste locally -- are you suggesting a modification of current sewage systems in tandem with development of vertical farms?  \n\nOverall, this is a very interesting article with some compelling arguments to support a move toward the city for farms.  What have the developments been over the past 5 years since it was written?  Thanks!!','2013-09-18 19:50:54'),(143,95,'carmen','carmenduijvelshoff@me.com','Thorough overview! Thnx! ','2013-10-10 18:06:04'),(144,1,'Margje Vlasveld','margje@ideewinkel.nl','Ik zie weinig recente activiteit, ben benieuwd naar ontwikkelingen en wil ook graag weten waar de benodigde voeding voor de gewassen vandaan komt.','2013-11-09 15:02:00'),(145,194,'Richard Kenward','Richard@artisan-digital-services.co.uk','Perhaps I\'ve missed something but I do not see any reference to either warm edge spacer bars or soft coat glass. Both of these make a significant contribution to the performance of a standard double glazed unit.','2013-11-10 11:44:59'),(151,300,'henk daalder','henk.daalder@guldenlijn.nl','Laat Eneco de kreet \"samen gaan we voor duurzaam\" eerlijk invullen, door burgers als gelijkwaardige partners te zien.\nGa dan praten voor een eerlijke deal, verkoop windparken in stukjes.\nEn op een transparante manier, als open source product, waar je parameters van kiest, en waar het onderhandelen gaat over die parameters, zoals de prijs, hoeveel stroom het oplevert en waar omwonenden invloed op kunnen hebben, als eigenaar van een stukje windpark.\n\nHier is het open source product, in ontwikkeling.\nMeehelpen mag\nhttp://www.duurzamebrabanders.nl/Stukje_Nieuwbouw_Windpark\n ','2013-12-12 00:20:25'),(147,253,'J Weckbacher','jjayuu@aol.com','Would love to have a home like this.','2013-11-15 22:25:03'),(149,1,'Tom Bosschaert','tom@except.nl','Margje: We are currently working on investigating a variety of pilot locations for the first polydome. This necessarily takes time for such an innovative project. We hope to start developing the first pilot soon, but a wide variety of factors influence this, including political.\n\nInformation about the nutrition flows can be found in the book that\'s downloadable on this page.','2013-12-11 23:33:59'),(150,194,'Tom Bosschaert','tom@except.nl','Richard: That is correct. This investigation purely focuses on the performance of the actually glass, not its frame or construction method. Both frame and method, including the finishing and detailing indeed make a significant difference.','2013-12-11 23:35:35'),(152,300,'Merel','merel@except.nl','Hoi Henk, dank voor je bericht. \n\nInteressant project dat je deelt, bedankt. De praatplaat is bedoeld om zo\'n open en eerlijk gesprek te voeren waar jij het over hebt. Daar hoort het praten over hoe je de windturbine \'deelt\' zeker bij. \n\nMisschien vind je dit interessant, Eneco is samen met windcoÃ¶peratie de Windvogel ook een aandelenproject begonnen (http://www.groenestroomjagraag.nl/node/318). \n\nSucces met je project! \nMet vriendelijke groet, \nMerel','2013-12-13 10:41:57'),(153,305,'Poul Tvermoes','ptvermoes@hotmail.com','Looks very interesting and would love to be involved whre I can. Certainly cover most of the requirments. Thought not the 3 D requirment.\n\nLook forward to talking with you.\n\nCheers\n\nPoul\n\n','2013-12-19 12:11:25'),(154,1,'Mark Rhine','m.rhine@rhibafarms.com','www.Rhibafarms.com \nWe are small aquaponics farm in Chandler, Arizona. Love your concept, excited to read your downloads and wishing you the greatest of success! If you need a location for a pilot project in Arizona, USA, please contact me!','2014-01-11 19:35:30'),(155,201,'Tijn','tijn.schmits@except.nl','We are looking at making multiple versions in multiple languages!','2014-03-07 13:16:02'),(178,93,'Atanacio Luna','pluvinergy@gmail.com','What a nice fair summary, Thanks. \nYou might consider adding something about Pluvinergy to make this informative summary more complete. ','2014-08-02 22:58:56'),(177,95,'Jaap Wijnja','j.g.wijnja@pl.hanze.nl','Ik denk dat het een interessant boek is, maar het doneren lukt me niet.... Hoe kom ik nu aan die pdf?\nVriendelijke groet,\n\nJaap ','2014-04-21 16:45:33'),(175,243,'Robert Tucker Jr','rotujr13@gmail.com','Do you have room for people with associates in applied science, with the concentration on solar technology.','2014-03-31 04:14:54'),(176,323,'Nels','nelsnelson@gmail.com','hurr hurr hurr','2014-04-01 18:31:16'),(98,81,'Erik','','Nice TEDtalk by Adam Curtis.','2012-06-17 15:21:36'),(86,58,'Tijn','www.up-link.nl','The render is really photo-realistic. Wow..','2012-04-17 16:31:48'),(99,175,'A.Kilbourne','mcbewoners.wordpress.com','I\'m very interested in this project, because it fills a part in my need to feed the poor and the masses, with local-grown food , and no-waste solutions on water, energy and material. I\'d like to know how small,local social-bussinness fits in the plan to make a better environment.\r\n\r\nThe direction for this project is closed-system urban farming, with return on energy and waiste-treatment.\r\n\r\nI\'d like to hear from you , from your point of view.\r\n\r\nAdrian Kilbourne,\r\nModus Operrandii','2012-07-13 19:12:13'),(95,90,'Sander Holt','','I love shared space as a method to revitalize urban areas. In the US specifically many downtown areas could be improved by applying these ideas.','2012-05-08 04:41:33'),(179,92,'Don Kirkpatrick','donkirk10@gmail.com','My lady has lupus. Exposure to UV (in the solar spectrum, e.g. and \"daylight\" fluorescent bulbs) makes her very ill.\n\nIt appears that residential \"white\" LED lamps have little or no UV output - is this essentially correct?\n\nThank you for an exhaustive explanation, Mr Spiers ','2014-09-15 06:21:30'),(180,92,'Don Kirkpatrick','donkirk10@gmail.com','My lady has lupus. Exposure to UV (in the solar spectrum, e.g. and \"daylight\" fluorescent bulbs) makes her very ill.\n\nIt appears that residential \"white\" LED lamps have little or no UV output - is this essentially correct?\n\nThank you for an exhaustive explanation, Mr Spiers ','2014-09-15 06:21:41'),(181,1,'Jason Blake','jason.blake7@bigpond.com','Hello,\n\nI am very interested in Greenhouse technology and have been since I watched a documentary by the BBC on Almeria, Spain. I live in Australia and while we have large land spaces, mostly we are limited by water availablity and weather conditions....\n\nHowever, China and the wide Asian region are demanding quality produce, yet Australia according to the Agricultural Minister Barnaby Joyce and Head of Australian Meat Industries say\'s we are at full production.\n\nI disagree. I believe through the use of Greenhouses bordering Cities and regional centres (with a supplement out door HEMP crop) that we can meet the demand asked of our neigbours.\n\nI am currently trying to put a business case together so I can access Cash Captial to purchase at least 5 acres with the intention of going to 100 acres, to build and run Greenhouses with a variety of crops.\n\nI really like your view point on having mulitple crops in the one spot. Works well with crop rotation and soil nutrition. (I have my own trade secrets I will add).\n\nWhat I need is an idea or rough estimate of how much it cost to construct one large size greenhouse and if it just turn over one type of crop, the tonnage per year.\n\nYou can understand that if I approach a Bank Manager and the Government with out some initial broad estimate costs, then I will not get anywhere. Also I would like to strike up a relationship with you because if I am successful with funding I will require as much specialized knowledge as I can get.','2014-09-23 07:08:56');
